I"ð<h2 id="create-your-blog-locally">Create your blog locally</h2>

<h3 id="1--install-all--prerequisites">1.  Install all  <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/installation/">prerequisites</a>.</h3>

<p>1&gt; Open terminal</p>

<p>2&gt; Check your Ruby
Before installing jekyll, we need to ensure the correct version of ruby . (Ruby version must be 2.5 or higher) .Check your Ruby version using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ruby -v</code></p>

<p>3&gt; Check your Gems
Check your Gems version using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">gem -v</code></p>

<h3 id="2--install-the-jekyll-and-bundler--gems">2.  Install the jekyll and bundler  <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/ruby-101/#gems">gems</a>.</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>```
gem install jekyll bundler
```
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="3--create-a-new-jekyll-site-at--myblog">3.  Create a new Jekyll site at  <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">./myblog</code>.</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>```
jekyll new myblog  
```
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="4--change-into-your-new-directory">4.  Change into your new directory.</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>``` 
cd myblog  
```
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>####5.  Build the site and make it available on a local server.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>```
bundle exec jekyll serve
```
</code></pre></div></div>

<ol>
  <li>Browse to  <a href="http://localhost:4000/">http://localhost:4000</a></li>
</ol>
:ET